issue.title: [Intl] Support ISO 3166-1 country codes
issue.body:
Hi,

I was wondering if we could extend the `CountryType` via an option to make it support ISO_3166-1 Alpha-3 country codes as listed here:

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1_alpha-3

I'm currently working on a project where I need country codes as 3 characters instead of just 2.

Would it be possible to include a new `alpha3` option or something to support 3 characters country codes? 

Edit: I saw that @umpirsky already compiled a list of all countries data in several formats: http://dev.umpirsky.com/list-of-all-countries-in-all-languages-and-all-data-formats. I don't see any ISO 3166 support in these files...

@fabpot @bschussek any thoughts?

comment.body: This is being worked on in #9206.

issue.title: en_GB locale and missing currency selection options
issue.body:
Hi,

Recently #8564 resolved an issue where locales like en_GB where not displaying all possible values in the selection boxes for country and language. 

I'm seeing this issue in Symfony 2.3.5 occur for currency selections as well. 

For example, the following two screen grabs show the currency selection box for "en" and "en_GB" respectively:

![currency](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/5579615/1302936/7e2bc65a-3142-11e3-9968-7ae83f430698.PNG)

Clearly the "en_GB" locale is missing a lot of the options that are shown in the "en" locale list.

comment.body: @fhendrikx Thank you for reporting! This is being worked on in #9206.

issue.title: [2.4.x-dev] Web Debug Toolbar
issue.body:
Hey!

I was using Symfony 2.4.0-BETA1 and since I have upgraded to Symfony 2.4.x-dev (master), the web debug toolbar disappears. After debugging, I notice there is no files created in the `app/cache/{env}/profiler/{dir}/{dir}` directory. The directories are created at every requests but there is no files inside them.

As everything works fine with Symfony 2.4.0-BETA1, I think there is probably a regression somewhere & so, open this issue.

comment.body: After debugging a little bit more, it is also relevant for Symfony 2.4.0-BETA1. If I create a service where I inject the `templating.form.renderer` or the `twig.form.renderer`, then the WDT disappears.

issue.title: [Form] Add option to disable 'extra fields' validation
issue.body:
Consider situation
```
$form = $formFactory->createNamedBuilder('', 'form', [], ['csrf_protection' => false])
     ->add('a', 'integer')
     ->setMethod('GET')
    ->getForm()
;
$form->handleRequest($this->getRequest());
var_dump($form->isValid());
```

now on example.com/test.php?a=1 form is valid. but on example.com/test.php?a=1&utm_source=zzz&... form is invalid, because there are extra fields

So i request an option, to disable extra fields validation

comment.body: @stof yes, my fault. And what about an option like ignore_extra_fields or allow_extra_fields?
